l experience in carrying out works under the approval<ul><li>or each piece of drilling equipment is operated by an employee who has a certificate of general training</li></ul></li><li>personnel undergo training every 5 years</li><li>personnel must have good and suitable equipment</li><li>only carry out works around classified establishments if the necessary permit or deeds are in place, report the commencement of the works in advance via the <a href=\"https://www.dov.vlaanderen.be/page/e-dov-meldpunt-boringen\">e-DOV</a> drilling <a href=\"https://www.dov.vlaanderen.be/page/e-dov-meldpunt-boringen\">hotline</a> and strictly adhere to the applicable environmental conditions</li><li>keeping an inventory of the supervisors of all works carried out over the past 5 years, each with the unique code obtained from the Subsoil Database Flanders, a drilling report and the date of the permit or deed, or a declaration that the works were carried out for a non-classified installation</li><li>submit an inventory of the drilling works carried out via the <a href=\"https://www.dov.vlaanderen.be/page/e-dov-meldpunt-boringen\">e-DOV hotline</a> at least every 2 months.</li></ul><p>On the website of the Flemish Environment Agency you will find <a href=\"https://www.vmm.be/water/grondwater/erkende-boorbedrijven\">more info on the obligations for recognised drilling companies</a>.</p>",
