            "nl": "<p>Om erkend te worden als ‘milieudeskundige bodemcorrosie’, moet u voldoen aan:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">algemene erkenningsvoorwaarden</a> die gelden voor alle erkenningen leefmilieu:<ul><li>In de 3 jaar die de aanvraag van het Vlaamse erkenningsbewijs voorafgaan, heeft de aanvrager geen strafrechtelijke veroordeling opgelopen in een <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">lidstaat van de Europees Economische Ruimte</a>, voor overtredingen van de milieuwetgeving rond het gebruik van de erkenning</li><li>in de 2 jaar die de aanvraag van het Vlaamse erkenningsbewijs voorafgaan, werd bij de aanvrager geen erkenning met hetzelfde voorwerp opgeheven, wegens de schending van de bijbehorende verplichtingen van die erkenning.</li></ul></li><li>bijzondere erkenningsvoorwaarden:<ul><li>een <strong>natuurlijke persoon </strong>zijn;</li><li>minstens <strong>de graad van bachelor</strong> uit een opleiding vermeld in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36561&amp;woLang=nl\">bijlage 5 van het VLAREL</a> of een daarmee gelijkgeschakelde graad hebben behaald<ul><li>en minstens <strong>1 jaar praktische ervaring</strong> hebben in de discipline bodemcorrosie, verworven <strong>binnen 5 jaar voorafgaand</strong> aan de erkenningsaanvraag.</li></ul></li><li>of minstens een <strong>diploma secundair onderwijs</strong> of een gelijkwaardig getuigschrift hebben behaald <ul><li>en minstens <strong>5 jaar praktische ervaring</strong> hebben in de discipline bodemcorrosie, verworven <strong>binnen 10 jaar voorafgaand</strong> aan de erkenningsaanvraag. </li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><p>Meer info vindt u in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">art. 8 VLAREL (algemene erkenningsvoorwaarden)</a> en <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36062&amp;woLang=nl\">art. 10 VLAREL (bijzondere erkenningsvoorwaarden)</a>. </p><h3>Geldigheidsduur en verplichtingen</h3><p>De erkenning is geldig voor <strong>onbepaald duur</strong>. Als ‘milieudeskundige bodemcorrosie’ moet u wel voldoen aan enkele verplichtingen (= gebruikseisen). </p><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-milieudeskundige-bodemcorrosie\">Meer info over de verplichtingen voor erkende milieudeskundigen</a>. </p>",
            "en-x-generated": "<p>To be recognised as an 'environmental expert on soil corrosion', you must meet:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all environmental recognitions:<ul><li>In the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not incurred any criminal conviction in a <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">Member State of the European Economic Area</a> for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li>special conditions of recognition:<ul><li>be a <strong>natural person </strong>;</li><li>have obtained at least <strong>the bachelor's degree</strong> from a course listed in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36561&amp;woLang=nl\">annex 5 of the VLAREL</a> or an equivalent degree<ul><li>and have at least <strong>1 year of practical experience</strong> in the discipline of soil corrosion, acquired <strong>within 5 years prior</strong> to the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>or have obtained at least a <strong>secondary school diploma</strong> or an equivalent certificate <ul><li>and at least <strong>5 years of</strong> practical experience in the discipline of soil corrosion, acquired within <strong>10</strong> years prior to the application for recognition. </li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><p>More information can be found in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">art. 8 VLAREL (general conditions for recognition)</a> and <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36062&amp;woLang=nl\">art. 10 VLAREL (special conditions for recognition)</a>. </p><h3>Period of validity and obligations</h3><p>The recognition is valid for <strong>an indefinite</strong> period. However, as an 'environmental expert soil corrosion' you must meet a number of obligations (= user requirements). </p><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-milieudeskundige-bodemcorrosie\">More info on the obligations for recognised environmental experts</a>. </p>",
            "en": "<p>To be recognised as an ‘environmental expert in soil corrosion’, you must fulfil:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all recognitions relating to the environment<ul><li>in the 3 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, the applicant has not been convicted of a criminal offence in a member state of the European Economic Area, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition.</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object was revoked due to infringement of the obligations associated with that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special recognition conditions</strong>:<ul><li>be a natural person</li><li>hold at least a <strong>bachelor’s </strong>degree in a subject stated in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36561&amp;woLang=nl\">annex 5 of the ‘VLAREL’</a> or an equivalent certificate<ul><li>having at least 1 year’s practical experience in the field of soil corrosion, obtained within the 5 years preceding the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>or have obtained at least a <strong>secondary education qualification</strong> or an equivalent certificate<ul><li>having at least 5 years’ practical experience in the field of soil corrosion, obtained within the 10 years preceding the application for recognition.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h2><strong>Validity period and obligations</strong></h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. As an ‘environmental expert in soil corrosion’, you must meet the following obligations among others to retain your recognition:</p><ul><li>hold <strong>insurance </strong>for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li>pay the <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\">annual fee</a>. The first payment is to be made in the year following the year in which you obtained the recognition. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-milieudeskundige-bodemcorrosie\">More info on the obligations for recognised environmental experts</a></p>",
