            "en": "<p>To be recognised as an environmental verifier for the environmental audit as defined by the DABM, you must fulfil:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> (page in Dutch) that apply to all the recognitions relating to the environment<ul><li>in the 3 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition, the applicant has not been convicted of a criminal offence in a member state of the European Economic Area, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition, no recognition of the applicant with the same subject was revoked due to infringement of the obligations associated with that recognition.</li></ul></li><li>and the following <strong>special recognition condition</strong>:<ul><li>hold the title of environmental verifier with regard to the voluntary participation of organisations in an <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/en/emas\">eco-management and audit scheme (EMAS)</a>. This title is governed by Regulation (EC) No. 1221/2009 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 25 November 2009. </li></ul></li></ul><h2>Validity Period and obligations</h2><p>Recognition as an environmental verifier for the environmental audit as defined by the DABM is granted for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. However, the environmental verifier must comply with some of the requirements of use for the recognition</p>"
