            "en-x-generated": "<p>Once all the above steps are in place, the organisation should apply for <strong>registration with the competent authority</strong>. The competent authority is <strong>the region </strong>where either the organisation or its headquarters are located. For <strong>the Flemish </strong>region, the <strong>Department of Environment and Spatial</strong> Development of the Flemish government is competent.</p><p>The application must be drawn up in <strong>Dutch </strong>and contain the following information/documents.</p><ul><li>The <strong>validated environmental statement</strong>, complying with the requirements of Annex IV of the regulation and clearly specifying and reporting at least the main environmental impacts of each site subject to registration.</li><li>A <strong>statement signed by the environmental verifier</strong> as referred to in Annex VII of the Regulation. In it the environmental verifier confirms that the verification and validation were carried out in accordance with the Regulation.</li><li>A <strong>completed form</strong> containing at least the information set out in Annex VI of the Regulation.</li></ul><p>The application must</p><ul><li>submitted via the <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/natuur-milieu-en-klimaat/erkenning-als-technicus-deskundige-opleidingscentrum-of-labo/erkenningenloket-omgeving\">online counter of the Department of Environment and Spatial Development</a> (click on \"Go to the accreditation counter\", log in with e-ID)</li><li>or sent by registered mail to:<br>Department of Environment and Spatial Development<br>Spatial development, Environmental Planning and Projects Division<br>Boulevard du Roi Albert II 20 bus 8<br>1000 Brussels</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/vrijwillige-milieuaudit-emas\">Additional information on EMAS registration</a> can be found on the website of the Department of Environment and Spatial Development.</p>",
            "nl-BE-x-generated-informal": "<p>Zodra alle bovenstaande stappen in orde zijn, moet de organisatie <strong>een aanvraag tot registratie indienen bij de bevoegde instantie</strong>. De bevoegde instantie is <strong>het gewest </strong>waar ofwel de organisatie ofwel de hoofdzetel gelegen is. Voor <strong>het Vlaamse gewest </strong>is het <strong>Departement Omgeving</strong> van de Vlaamse overheid bevoegd.</p><p>De aanvraag moet in het <strong>Nederlands </strong>opgesteld worden en onderstaande gegevens/stukken bevatten.</p><ul><li>De <strong>gevalideerde milieuverklaring</strong>, die voldoet aan de vereisten van bijlage IV van de verordening en waar minimaal de belangrijkste milieueffecten duidelijk worden gespecificeerd en gerapporteerd van elke vestiging, onderhavig aan de registratie.</li><li>Een <strong>door de milieuverificateur ondertekende verklaring</strong> als bedoeld in bijlage VII van de verordening. Hierin bevestigt de milieuverificateur dat de verificatie en validering overeenkomstig de verordening werden uitgevoerd.</li><li>Een <strong>ingevuld formulier</strong> dat ten minste de informatie bevat zoals beschreven in bijlage VI van de verordening.</li></ul><p>De aanvraag moet</p><ul><li>ingediend worden via het <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/natuur-milieu-en-klimaat/erkenning-als-technicus-deskundige-opleidingscentrum-of-labo/erkenningenloket-omgeving\">online loket van het Departement Omgeving</a> (klik op “Ga naar het erkenningenloket”, aanmelden met e-ID)</li><li>of aangetekend per post verzonden worden naar:<br/>Departement Omgeving<br/>Afdeling Gebiedsontwikkeling, Omgevingsplanning en -projecten<br/>Koning Albert-II-laan 20 bus 8<br/>1000 Brussel</li></ul><p>Op de website van het Departement Omgeving vind je <a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/vrijwillige-milieuaudit-emas\">bijkomende informatie over de EMAS-registratie</a>.</p>",
            "en": "<p>Once all the above steps have been completed, the organisation must <strong>submit an application for registration</strong> to the competent body. The competent body is the region where either the organisation or the headquarters are located. <strong>The Department of Environment and Spatial Development</strong> (Dutch: Departement Omgeving) of the Flemish administration is competent for the Flemish Region. </p><p>The application must be drawn up in <strong>Dutch </strong>and include the information/documents listed below. </p><ul><li>The <strong>validated environmental statement</strong> that meets the requirements of Annex IV of the Regulation and clearly identifies and reports at least the most significant environmental impacts of each site subject to registration. </li><li>A <strong>declaration signed by the environmental verifier</strong> as referred to in Annex VII of the Regulation. The environmental verifier confirms in this declaration that the verification and validation were carried out in compliance with the Regulation. </li><li>A <strong>completed form</strong> containing at least the information set out in Annex VI to the Regulation. </li></ul><p>The application must</p><ul><li>be submitted through the <a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/erkenningenloket\" target=\"_blank\">online desk of the Department of Environment and Spatial Development</a> (click on “Ga naar het erkenningenloket’’, log in with e-ID) </li><li>or be sent by registered letter to: <br>Departement Omgeving <br>Afdeling Gebiedsontwikkeling, Omgevingsplanning en -projecten <br>Koning Albert-II-laan 20 bus 8 <br>1000 Brussel </li></ul><p>You can find <a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/vrijwillige-milieuaudit-emas\" target=\"_blank\">additional information on EMAS registration</a> on the website of the Department of Environment and Spatial Development. </p>",
